SIMPLE: phobia
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: phobia
<hw>pho"bi*a</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"b⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Any irrational and persistent fear, whether of a situation,
activity, or object; a phobia typically leads to a strong desire to
avoid the object of the phobia.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> phobic disorder, phobic neurosis.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-phobia</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: -phobia
<hw>-pho"bi*a</hw> <pr>(f⟦omac⟧"b⟦esl⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr> <pos>suffix</pos>
<def>A combining form used as a suffix to designate specific phobias,
such as agora<ex>phobia</ex> (fear of public places),
acro<ex>phobia</ex> (fear of heights). The first part of the combining
form is usually derived from Greek.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>phobic</ent>⟦br⟧
